## **The @mention intelligence:**

### **Who to mention based on context:**

```javascript
function determineMentions(message, conflicts) {
  let mentions = [];

  // Always mention leadership roles
  const leadership = ['@president', '@vp', '@treasurer'];
  mentions.push(...leadership);

  // If high-severity conflicts, mention everyone
  if (conflicts.some(c => c.severity === 'HIGH')) {
    mentions.push('@everyone');
  }

  // If message already mentioned specific people, mention them back
  const userMentions = message.mentions.users.map(u => `@${u.username}`);
  mentions.push(...userMentions);

  // Deduplicate
  return [...new Set(mentions)].join(' ');
}
```

