## 1. `find_best_pair()` - Finding the Most Frequent Adjacent Token Pair

### Purpose
Scan the entire corpus to find which adjacent token pair appears most frequently.

### Detailed Implementation Strategy

```c
int find_best_pair(Sentence corpus[], int corpus_size, char* best_left, char* best_right) {
    int max_frequency = 0;
    bool found_any_pair = false;

    // We need to count ALL possible adjacent pairs
    // Strategy: Use nested loops to compare every possible pair

    // First pass: find all unique pairs and count them
    for (int sent_idx = 0; sent_idx < corpus_size; sent_idx++) {
        Sentence *sentence = &corpus[sent_idx];

        // For each adjacent pair in this sentence
        for (int i = 0; i < sentence->token_count - 1; i++) {
            char *left_token = sentence->tokens[i];
            char *right_token = sentence->tokens[i + 1];

            // Count how many times this EXACT pair appears in ENTIRE corpus
            int pair_frequency = 0;

            // Second pass: count this specific pair across all sentences
            for (int count_sent = 0; count_sent < corpus_size; count_sent++) {
                Sentence *count_sentence = &corpus[count_sent];

                for (int j = 0; j < count_sentence->token_count - 1; j++) {
                    if (strcmp(count_sentence->tokens[j], left_token) == 0 &&
                        strcmp(count_sentence->tokens[j + 1], right_token) == 0) {
                        pair_frequency++;
                    }
                }
            }

            // Check if this is the best pair so far
            // IMPORTANT: If frequencies are equal, choose the first one encountered
            if (pair_frequency > max_frequency) {
                max_frequency = pair_frequency;
                strcpy(best_left, left_token);
                strcpy(best_right, right_token);
                found_any_pair = true;
            }
        }
    }

    return max_frequency;
}
```

### Key Details:
- **Double counting prevention**: The nested loop approach naturally handles this
- **Tie-breaking**: First pair encountered with max frequency wins (left-to-right corpus order)
- **Return value**: The frequency count of the best pair (0 if no pairs exist)

